Supplementary infromation for article by Tahovská et al. (20xx) "Positive response of soil microbes to long-term nitrogen input in spruce forest: results from Gårdsjön whole-catchment N addition experiment", doi:xxxxxxx

Supplementary table 1:
The most abundant phyla in all prokaryotic sequences (all that have at least 1% in one of the categories; the most abundant classes of Proteobacteria shown as well) and most abundant fungal genera among all fungal sequences, including their lifestyles (ecm – ectomycorrhizal, yeast, mould – saprotrophic; all that have at least 2% in one of the categories) in organic and mineral soils of control and N addition catchments and in their dry and wet parts. Mean ± SD are given (n=6–8). Results of factorial ANOVAs (F values) of the effects of N addition (N), horizon (organic; mineral) and moisture (wet; dry) and selected interactions (N x moisture; N x horiyon] are presented. Statistical significances of F values are marked as follows: + p<0.05, ++ p<0.01, +++ p<0.001, ns – not significant. Asterisks mark statistical significances (* p<0.05, ** p<0.01, *** p<0.001) of post-hoc comparison (Tukey HSD test) between controls and N-additions within dry/wet parts of catchments and for organic/mineral horizons separately.
